<apex:page standardController="Booking__c" renderAs="pdf" extensions="convertValueToWords"  showHeader="false" sidebar="false" applyHtmlTag="false" applyBodyTag="false"  standardStylesheets="false" >
    <html >
        <head>
            <style type="text/css" media="print">
                @page {
                margin-bottom: 200px;
                @bottom-right {
                
                content: "Page " counter(page);
                
                }
                }
                @top-center {
                content: element(header);
                }
                @bottom-left {
                content: element(footer);
                }
                }
                div.header {
                padding: 10px;
                position: running(header);
                }
                div.footer {
                display: block;
                padding: 5px;
                position: running(footer);
                }
                .pagenumber:before {
                content: counter(page);
                }
                .pagecount:before {
                content: counter(pages);
                }
                div.header {
                padding: 20px;
                position: running(header);
                margin-left: -200px;
                }
                div.footer {
                padding: 10px;
                position: running(footer);
                font-size: 9px;
                text-align:left;
                
                }
                div.footer :first-child{
                text-align:right;
                }
                
                div.content, div.content p{
                padding:0 20px;
                line-height:1.5;
                font-size:14px;
                }
                th, td {
                padding: 5px;
                }
                p{
                line-height:1;
                padding:1px;
                font-size:16px;
                }
                div{
                line-height:1;
                padding:1px;
                }
                table, tr {
                border: 1px solid black;
                border-collapse: collapse;
                }
                .content{
                font-size:14px;
                }
                .content-wrapper {
                page-break-inside: avoid;
                }
            </style> 
        </head>
        <body>
            <div class="content" >
                <apex:outputPanel >
                    
                    <div >
                        <p style="text-align:center;font-size:15px;">
                            <strong><u> MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING</u></strong>
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:center">
                            <strong>This MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING</strong> is executed at Bengaluru on this <apex:outputText value="{0, date, dd MMMM yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> BY AND BETWEEN:
                        </p>
                        <p style="text-align:justify;font-size:15px;">
                            <strong>M/s SOWPARNIKA HOMES PRIVATE LIMITED,</strong>a Company incorporated under the Companies Act 2013, having its
                            Registered Office at No.750, ‘C’ Block, 1st Main Road, AECS Lay out, Kundalahalli, Bangalore-560037 represented by its 
                            authorized signatory {!Booking__c.Authorized_Signato__c}, Authorized vide board resolution dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Authorized_Signatory_Resolution_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText>. Hereinafter called the FIRST
                            PARTY (which expression shall, wherever the context so admits or requires, mean and include its successors-in-interest, legal 
                            representatives, executors, administrators and assigns) on the<strong>FIRST PART.</strong>
                        </p>
                        <div style="font-size:15px;padding-left:20px;text-align:center;">
                            AND 
                        </div>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;">{!Booking__c.First_Applicant_Name__c}, W/o/S/o/C/o. {!Booking__c.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}, Aged about  <apex:outputText value="{0, Number,###,###,###}"> <apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Age__c}" /></apex:outputText> years,<br/>
                            PAN No: {!Booking__c.PAN_Number__c}, Aadhar No. {!Booking__c.Aadhar_Number__c}.<br/><br/>
                            <apex:repeat value="{!Booking__c.Co_Applicants__r}" var="p">
                                {!p.Name}, W/o/S/o/C/o. {!p.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}, Aged about <apex:outputText value="{0, Number,###,###,###}"> <apex:param value="{!p.Age__c}" /></apex:outputText> years,<br/>
                                PAN No: {!p.PAN_Number__c}, Aadhar No. {!p.Aadhar_Number__c}.<br/><br/>
                            </apex:repeat>
                            Residing at {!Booking__c.Address__c}
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">Hereinafter called the SECOND PARTY (which term shall, wherever the context so admits or requires, mean and include his/her/their assigns successors, executors, administrators,
                            heirs &amp; legal representatives) on the <strong>SECOND PART.</strong></p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;"><strong>WHEREAS FIRST PARTY </strong>is sole and absolute owner and at peaceful possession and enjoyment of
                            residentially converted lands bearing Survey Numbers: 10/4 10/5, 10/6 ,10/7, 11/17, 12/1, 34/3 and 34/4,  
                            Katha No.1809, RDPR E- Khatha PID  No.1503002500522772, measuring in all 6 Acre 18 guntas, Situated at
                            Samethanahalli Village, Anugondanahalli Hobli, Hosakote Taluk, Bangalore Rural District which is more fully 
                            described in the Schedule-A hereunder hereinafter referred to as <strong>SCHEDULE A PROPERTY.</strong>  </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;"><strong>WHEREAS,</strong> the STRR Planning Authority has granted approval to develop the Project vide
                            Commencement Certificate No. STRRPA/TP/CC/188/2024-25, dated 24-12-2024, for construction of Basement, ground plus
                            Fourteen upper Floors of residential apartment building over the Schedule- ‘A’ Property. </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">
                            WHEREAS the FIRST PARTY has propounded a scheme of ownership units to be built on the Schedule “A” property 
                            comprising of residential apartments, (hereinafter called the said scheme) where under a persons interested in 
                            acquiring a unit in the building named as “SOWPARNIKA RHYTHM OF RAIN” being under construction on the Schedule “A”
                            property shall have to acquire a specific undivided right, title and interest in the land covered by the Schedule “A”
                            property by virtue whereof such persons will be granted the right to construct, own and enjoy a specific unit in the said
                            building with all matters of common concern, share, amenities, facilities, liabilities, etc., being looked after in terms of an
                            overall scheme and upon the completion of the said scheme, the land covered by the Schedule “A” property will be owned by all
                            such persons owning the units therein as co-owners.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;"><strong>AND WHEREAS</strong>pursuant to the above the FIRST PARTY have further offered the purchasers friendly scheme,
                            wherein the SECOND PARTY on the basis of the mutual understanding between the parties the SECOND PARTY have booked the flat in the
                            proposed residential project. </p> 
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">The parties have entered into agreement of sale and construction with certain terms and conditions. Based on the said
                            agreement First Party will provide all assistance to the SECOND PARTY to apply for a housing loan in the name of SECOND PARTY in order to
                            obtain the housing loan for purchase of the apartment unit. The FIRST PARTY herein has offer the reimbursement of Pre-EMI to the SECOND PARTY 
                            till May 2027. After that the second party shall be responsible to pay the   Pre- EMI/ EMI etc., to the respective bank/ financial institution.</p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">AND WHEREAS in the event of cancellation of the allotment of the apartment unit under this scheme, it is hereby agreed
                            between the parties that the agreement of sale and construction and this MOU entered between the parties shall stand cancelled.
                            The FIRST PARTY shall be entitled to forfeit the booking amount of the apartment cost thereafter shall refund the balance advance if any. 
                            The second party shall fully co-operate with the First Party to close the second party housing loan with bank or financial institution to the
                            extent of the Principal outstanding amount as on the date of settlement by the first party with the bank or financial institution </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">
                            WHEREAS pursuant to the above scheme and after completely understanding the above scheme and after satisfaction of the title and
                            plans approvals and other details of the FIRST PARTY, the SECOND PARTY being interested and decided to book the Apartment 
                            No. {!Booking__c.Unit_NumberFor__c} having Super built up area {!Booking__c.Built_up_area__c} Sq.ft, carpet area  {!Booking__c.Carpet_Area__c} Sq.ft, Balcony area {!Booking__c.Balcony_Area__c} Sq.ft on {!Booking__c.Floor__c} Floor
                            with  {!Booking__c.Parking__c} parking along with {!Booking__c.UDS__c} square feet of undivided share of land which is more-fully described in the Schedule B, here under 
                            and hereinafter referred to as Schedule B Property.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;">
                            AND WHEREAS pursuant to the above, the FIRST PARTY and SECOND PARTY have entered into an agreement
                            of sale and construction dated: <apex:outputText value="{0, date, dd MMMM yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> herein for sale of Schedule B Property.
                        </p>
                         <p style="text-align:center;font-size:15px;">
                            <strong><u> NOW THIS MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING WITHNESSTH AS FOLLOWS:</u></strong>
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">1.	The SECOND PARTY has on the date of signing of the MOU paid the
                            amount of Rs {!totlreceivedinIndian}/- (Rupees {!tillDateReceived} only) for Schedule “B” &amp; “C” Property.</p>
                        <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">2.	The SECOND PARTY hereby agrees to fully co-operate with the FIRST PARTY for applying and 
                            obtaining the home loan from the bank or financial institution. Wherein the processing fee shall be borne by the SECOND
                            PARTY.</p>
                         <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">3.	The SECOND PARTY also fully agrees to sign all the loan agreements, documents, forms,
                             undertakings, and any other documents required for obtaining home loan and co-operate   fully with the FIRST PARTY or with bank representatives.</p>
                         <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">4.	The FIRST PARTY hereby agrees to reimburse the Pre-EMI based on disbursements to the SECOND PARTY 
                             till May 2027. After that SECOND PARTY shall be responsible for payment of interest/ Pre- EMI/ EMI etc., to the respective
                             bank/financial institution. The SECOND PARTY also agrees to make the payment of balance consideration towards the flat, registration 
                             expenses, stamp duty and miscellaneous charges at the time of registration of the sale deed of the apartment. In this context the term
                             intimation of readiness for possession will mean that the apartment is ready for livable condition and does not include the full 
                             completion of all amenities and services.</p>
                         <p style="font-size:15px;text-align:justify;">5.	In the event the SECOND PARTY desires to cancel the said allotment of apartment, the SECOND PARTY
                             shall intimate the same in writing to the FIRST PARTY and on receipt of such communication from the SECOND PARTY this MOU,
                             agreement of sale and construction shall automatically stands cancelled, and the FIRST PARTY shall repay the housing loan 
                             to the respective financial institution as per RERA rules for which Second Party shall fully cooperate with the FIRST PARTY.
                        </p>
                        <div style="page-break-after:always;"></div> 
